
Here's the good way:


The main function {
    That arbitrary class constructor()
    saving that arbitrary class's variable to a different variable because you wanted to use it
    actual code (05)
    arbitrary class's method that saves some data()
}

A different utility class {
    some variable
    a tiny utility function that's also only used once {
        actual code (01)
        usage of this variable
    }
    
    an unused function {
        actual code
    }
}

an arbitrary class {
    another variable definition

    Constructor {
        a random function that's only used once and is defined right next to it's definition()
    }

    that random function that's only used once and is defined right next to it's definition {
        actual code (00)
        that tiny utility function that's also only used once()
        usage of the before defined variable
        actual code (02)
        a method that saves some data ()
    }

    a method that saves some data {
        actual code (03) (06)
        actual code (04) (07)
    }
}



