Here's an alternative architecture for the same ammount of code, but who would ever structure it like this, it's too short like this!



The main function {
    actual code (00)
    actual code (01)
    some variable definition
    usage of the variable
    another variable definition
    usage of the second variable
    actual code (02)
    a function that saves some data()
    actual code (05)
    a function that saves some data()
}

a function that saves some data {
    actual code (03) (06)
    actual code (04) (07)
}

